          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The new transaction is nested within the threadâ€™s current transaction, if there is one."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The first time you modify the scene graph during a pass through the run loop, SceneKit automatically creates a transaction and makes it the current transaction. (SceneKit commits that transaction when the next iteration of the run loops begins.) If you call this method to create a custom transaction before modifying the scene graph, your custom transaction becomes the current transaction."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
